keel.Algorithms.Neural_Networks.NNEP_Common.mutators.parametric

Class ParametricSAMutator<I extends NeuralNetIndividual>

  • java.lang.Object
    • <any>
      • keel.Algorithms.Neural_Networks.NNEP_Common.mutators.NeuralNetMutator<I>
        • keel.Algorithms.Neural_Networks.NNEP_Common.mutators.parametric.ParametricMutator<I>
          • keel.Algorithms.Neural_Networks.NNEP_Common.mutators.parametric.ParametricSAMutator<I>
  • Type Parameters:
    I - Type of individuals to mutate

    public class ParametricSAMutator<I extends NeuralNetIndividual>
extends ParametricMutator<I>

    Parametric mutator for neural nets, mutate the weights of the neural nets mutated. This implementation uses a Simulated Annealing method to update alpha values. IMPORTANT NOTE: Parametric mutator works directly with he individuals instead of returning a mutated copy of them. This is for performance reasons. If you want to use another mutator you have to consider that individuals will be changed when you use parametric mutation

    Since:
    JDK1.5

    Version:
    0.1
    Author:
    Written by Pedro Antonio Gutierrez Penia (University of Cordoba) 16/7/2007, Written by Aaron Ruiz Mora (University of Cordoba) 16/7/2007
